S'[Laughs] Well, it\xe2\x80\x99s a good question, but apparently not enough people are asking it because quite a few people would like to have it. I have this position not for any personal reasons, it is because I feel a deep mission to protect the Jewish people and the one and only Jewish state. We\xe2\x80\x99ve had a horrible history on the soil of Europe. Our people were murdered \xe2\x80\x93 six million of our people and from the ashes of the Holocaust, we built the state. This state is being attacked again and again by Arab states and now by Iranian-backed terrorists. And it\xe2\x80\x99s being attacked again and again with slander. In our history, including on the soil of Europe, we had a regular pattern. First the Jewish people were maligned, then they were attacked. And the maligning, the vilification served as the legitimization for the attacks that followed, and in many ways this is what is happening to the State of Israel.It is vilified again and again in public opinion, including in European public opinion, to prepare the attacks. And people don\xe2\x80\x99t know the facts. They don\xe2\x80\x99t know that we were attacked from the areas that we\xe2\x80\x99re now asked to return. They don\xe2\x80\x99t know that when we vacated territories in Gaza, once we walked out, Iran immediate walked in and they fired rockets on us. Can people seriously ask us to just walk away? To vacate all this area? Can they seriously tell us you have no connection to these areas? These areas where Abraham, Isaac and Jacob walked, where my ancestors walked, where Jews have been for thousands of years? I\xe2\x80\x99m not saying that we don\xe2\x80\x99t recognize that there\xe2\x80\x99s another people there. I do, and I want a peace with them. And I\xe2\x80\x99m prepared for them to have their own state, but I don\xe2\x80\x99t want to see a situation where we are completely erased, that we \xe2\x80\x93 who do not want to rule the Palestinians \xe2\x80\x93 have them establish another Iranian-backed terror state on the suburbs of Tel Aviv that threatens our very survival.'
